text:
Just incase anyone missed this nugget when it was added… comme moi — visibility apparently has an “advanced” rule where you can now string “And / Or ” operators together with multiple conditions….

```"visibility_rules" : "ADVANCED",
"advanced_visibility" : {
   "boolean_operator" : "AND",
   "criteria" : [{
     "controlling_field" : "field_name",
     "controlling_value_regex" : "regular_expression_in_controlling_field",
      "operator" : "MATCHES_REGEX"
    }, 
    {
     "controlling_field" : "field_name",
     "controlling_value_regex" : "regular_expression_in_controlling_field",
     "operator" : "EQUAL"
    }]
}```
<https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/cms/building-blocks/module-theme-fields-overview#field-visibility>
